column5: If you do snag'em.... snag'em in the dang eye!!!
Lake nosbonsing for the boys weekend for eyes and pike for me.
Lake nosbonsing for the boys weekend for eyes and pike for me.
Staying at Tumblhome Lodge, on Crotch Lake for the 7th straight year, great place to stay and always rainy, oh well at least its getting away from here.  Good luck to everyone this weekend.
Gloucester Pool - Sat 12:01am
At a Provincial Park on lower Simcoe for pike and weather permitting, some whities too.  and catching them all squarely in the mouth!
Well that was implied....LOL...just not sure where yet...
Quinte here we come!!!!!

Looks like Friday will be the best of wind and weather conditions for the whole weekend. I'm on graveyard shift so after I take the little one to school I'll be off in the kayak in search of big Mountsberg pike. Hope I don't fall asleep at the paddle
Spiel and myself jiggin for Whities on Simcoe Fri.   Then fish the Dofasco derby Sun. in Dunnville at Fishmasters.
Yup 4 days with the gang.Percher is a good dishwasher
Work, work more, and then work some more.

Doing a much-anticipated overnight Carping trip with some friends/fellow OFNers Fri-Sat.  Sunday and Monday are still open but it will probably be family time/yardwork time.  Good luck to all and have a fun, safe weekend!
Hey Mike at least my filleting knife gets used.And my livewell always smells like fish.

I'll be heading up to Nip for the weekend, enjoying the company of GOOD friends! I have already cleaned up my white bucket, loaded it to the brim with large and small marshmellows and am lookin forward to hookin/catchin anything willing to dine on my offerings! HH PS... i hope the bucket snares them in the mouth!
You look all ready!!!  Just don't forget your net  Have a great time...good luck and stay safe!
Thanks Cliff! I don't use a net, I just bring along my ski gloves and lip 'em! That, or they get stuck in the bucket, so who really needs a net! HH
Working at BPS Saturday and Monday, but will be on Bellwood on Sunday for our first CTTS Tourney of the year for Pike. You're welcome to join us.
Fish Kincardine derby, extra long weekend  sat to sat.
Hitting the lower Rideau system for some crappies and pike!!!
For me, it's naturally fuelled mayhem in Algonquin Park, chasing brookies and eyes, and gorging myself on marshmellows!!  Have a safe, fish filled weekend everybody!  HD
Off to Bracebridge for pike with the boyz on Saturday, got a wedding on Sunday and yardwork on Monday. Hopefully we slay the pike, whenever the weather sucks, we have nailed some really nice ones.

going to four mile lake here...  need to get the dock in, the boat lift in and then all the other spring cleaning done at the cottage.  then, if the dock is in (not sure if we can as the water is very high) MAYBE get out on the lake with the my daughter.  thanks for the reminder too about the marshmellows, she loves em...
No fishing for me, working Sat. then going to a wedding after that, working Sunday and Monday, now that I know BPS is open Monday I may stop in on my way home.  Maureen
Stop by and say hi Maureen.

Can't seem to find the weekend fishing thread from before, anyway this weekend im going camping from friday to monday. Campbellford were goin to gonna try for lots of panfish.  What is everyone else doing???
Hitting up Lower Buckhorn lake and will try a few other lakes around upper and lower Buckhorn.

Going about 5 hours north to a friend's cottage around North Bay.. pretty excited for a weekend of bbq, beer, and testing out a whole whack of new walleye and northern pike lures. My goal for the weekend is a few walleye's for the pan, and a few nice northern's for the sport..
Brookies and blackflies for me this weekend. Might get lucky and hook into an inland rainbow/splake/laker while im at it.  I'll try not to snag them  Sinker
Pigeon Lake for me.  Heading up tomorrow for a solid 4 days of givin er!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!   Have a great 2 4 boys!  cheers ff
The Saugeen in Durham and Lake Eugenia Fri to Mon for us.
Northern Quebec
I'm lucky....I can see Lake Nipissing from my window!  Thats where I will be fishing this weekend
Annual 4 day pickeral trip to Quinte
I'll be ripping X-raps in Muskoka for some tasty walleye!!!!!!!!!!    AFter I work on Saturday
Leaving 2am Friday for the French River - one day of cottage clean and set up and 3 days of Pickeral and Pike Fishing with my 2 kids
~~Usual partner has to work 2 out of 3 days this weekend, looks like Sunday we"ll be out keeping an eye on the weather, could be on Rice for eyes, or Simcoe for Whities, or maybe Sparrow for Mr Pike
Probably the Grand in Dunnville or long point bay.  we'll see where the van stops
Must be a Dodge...lol
BWAHAHAHAHAHAHAH!!!  I will be on Nipissing  with some good friends  G
hi,  I might see SBCregal at long point after work on Sat.
I'll be in Perth on a small lake for tasty no motorboat walleyes and pikers!!! can't dang' wait.. first time out for the year!!!! starting to get the shakes!!!!
I'll be sitting right here looking at satellite shots of a frozen Lake Nipigon.

Lake Huron tribs for drop back rainbows  and then onto the Maitland for some crappies.  Maybe try some carp fishing in the Goderich marina/pier.  If the weather is crap, I am gonna have a big nap!  Good luck all...

Bly, my youngest and I will be hitting Sturgeon on Friday....spend all day there and then dinner at Big Cliff's place!  We'll be looking for crappie and walleye.  Practicing for a gig my band has in June on Saturday morning...then off to visit mom on Saturday.  Sunday and Monday are wide open at this point...not sure what to do.

work saterday was hoping to get away for two days. But i just got news tonight my dad has had two strokes so will be staying home.  He was sopost to be flying in with my mom  from the UK in three weeks for my grandparents 60th wedding anniversary.  What ever your doing have a great weekend and enjoy being with your loved ones.  Nauti.
Where in northern Quebec?  I'll be heading to Lac Nilgaut in semi-northern quebec.  Never been before but it looks like its a couple hours north of petawawa.
Point-au-baril Pike and Walleye hope the crap weather doesnt mess it up to much!!!!

Was going to the CTTS Tourney on Sunday but my wife made other plans.  We will be down at the cottage in Long Point for the weekend. I will get out there and get some pike and perch for sure.  BTW since I see a few of you are going down there, bring a shovel and help me dig out the snow fence if ya can   (Look for my truck on the beach side)
:dunno:You  could always go fishing
